        <td width="358" height="338" valign="top" class="maintext"><p align="left"><a href="news/index.htm"><br>
        </a>Comenius Yorkshire and the Humber support the implementation of the National Languages Strategy in the English regions and we specialise in advice, consultancy and training in all aspects of teaching and learning in the education sector including: </p>
              <ul>
                <li class="style18">Modern  Languages in the secondary sector </li>
                <li class="style18">Primary Languages </li>
                <li class="style18">Interactive Whiteboard Training </li>
                <li class="style18">Newly Qualified Teachers</li>
                <li class="style18">Regional Support Group for Early Language Learning</li>
                <li class="style18"> Subject Leadership</li>
                <li class="style18">Effective Team Building</li>
                <li class="style18">Staff Development</li>
                <li class="style18">Pupil Behaviour Management <br>
                    <br>
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p> Now funded by DfES through CILT, the National Centre for Languages, Comenius Centres are backing the National Languages Strategy and increasing their activity.<br>
                  <br>
                Comenius will be consulting those with a stake in language learning, publicising new initiatives and co-ordinating CPD opportunities for teachers.<br>
  <br>
                Comenius centres - named after the Renaissance scholar who originated the modern theory of childhood education and especially language learning - are hosted in nine English regions by a variety of organisations, such as local education authorities and providers of initial teacher training.<br>
  <br>
                Each regional manager is an experienced professional in language learning whose job is to build relationships with local education authorities, higher, further and adult education providers, Specialist Language Colleges, Advanced Skills Teachers, Learning and Skills Councils, Regional Language Networks and other stakeholders. The development of these networks is underpinned by the Comenius Network Manager based at CILT and links with other partners at a national level.</p>
